excerpt: Historic fort with reservoirs carved out of rock & lookouts with expansive views over Ajmer city.
name: Taragarh Fort - Ajmer
address: Taragarh Fort, Taragarh Rd, Taragarh, Ajmer, Rajasthan 305001, India

excerpt: One of India's oldest mosques, built in the Indo-Islamic style during the 1190s with many pillars.
detail_description: Adhai Din Ka Jhopra in Ajmer is a must-visit for history buffs and architecture enthusiasts. This ancient mosque, built in the 1190s, showcases exquisite Indo-Islamic architecture with intricate carvings, beautiful arches, and delicate screenwork. Originally a Sanskrit college and ruins of Hindu temples, it was transformed into a mosque by Mohammed Ghori.
name: Adhai Din Ka Jhopra - Ajmer
address: FJ4G+33J, Ander Kote Rd, Lakhan Kothri, Ajmer, Rajasthan 305001, India

excerpt: This artificial, 12th-century lake spreads over 13 kilometres, with hiking trails & boating.
detail_description: Anasagar Lake, located in the city of Ajmer in the Indian state of Rajasthan, is a picturesque 12th-century artificial lake spread over 13 kilometers. Built by Arnoraj Chauhan, it offers hiking trails and boating opportunities. The lake's stunning views make it a popular spot for photography, especially at dusk.
name: Anasagar Lake
address: Ajmer, Rajasthan

excerpt: Holy site honouring the revered 13th-century Muslim mystic & saint, home to his tomb & a mosque.
detail_description: The Hazrat Khwaja Gharib Nawaz Dargah is a revered Muslim mystic and saint's holy site, containing his tomb and a mosque. This sacred place in India attracts millions of devotees seeking blessings from Hazrat Khwaja Moinuddin Hasan Chishti, who is widely regarded as one of the world's leading spiritual healers.
name: Khwaja Gharib Nawaz Dargah Sharif
address: 111, Dargah Sharif, Khadim Mohalla, Diggi Bazaar, Ajmer, Rajasthan 305001, India

excerpt: Created for famine relief in 1892, this manmade lake features birding, picnic areas & green space.
detail_description: Foy Sagar Lake, situated in Ajmer, Rajasthan, is a stunning man-made lake built in 1892 to alleviate water scarcity during a severe famine. Nestled amidst the picturesque Aravalli hills, this serene lake offers visitors a tranquil escape from city life. Boasting lush green spaces and picnic areas, it's an ideal spot for birdwatching and leisurely strolls along its well-maintained promenade.
name: Varun Sagar Lake
address: Rajasthan 305005

excerpt: This massive, ornate Jain temple in the mountains mixes a variety of architectural styles.
detail_description: Nestled in the picturesque Aravali Mountains, the Nareli Gyanodaya Digambar Jain Temple is a stunning architectural gem located just outside Ajmer. This remarkable temple complex is dedicated to Lord Adinath, the first Tirthankara of Jainism, and showcases an impressive fusion of traditional and contemporary design elements. Visitors are treated to intricate carvings and vibrant colors that adorn its marble fa√ßade, making it a feast for the eyes.
name: Nareli Gyanodaya Digambar Jain Temple
address: Sri Dnyanoday Tirtha Area, Gyanoday Nagar, Nareli, Rajasthan 305024, India

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Ajmer, Rajasthan, Mayo College stands as a testament to India's rich educational heritage. Established in 1875 by the British colonial government and named after Richard Bourke, the 6th Earl of Mayo, this prestigious boarding school was designed to offer an elite education akin to that of Eton College in Britain. With its stunning architecture that harmoniously blends Rajasthani and British styles, Mayo College features striking red sandstone buildings set against lush green lawns and gardens.
name: Mayo College Ajmer
address: Srinagar Road, Alwar Gate, Rajasthan 305001, India

excerpt: 19th-century Jain temple complex featuring red sandstone structures & gold-plated wooden figures.
detail_description: SoniJi Ki Nasiya Digambar Jain Mandir is a 19th-century temple complex located in Ajmer, known as Lal Mandir due to its red sandstone structures. Dedicated to Lord Adinath, the first Jain 'Tirthankara', this two-storied building houses a prayer area and a museum. The museum showcases a gallery made of gold depicting the five stages of Lord Adinath's life.
name: Soni Ji Ki Nasiya Jain Temple
address: Prithivi Raj Marg, Dumada, Dargah Bazar, Ajmer, Rajasthan 305001, India

detail_description: The Victoria Jubilee Clock Tower in Ajmer, Rajasthan is a significant landmark that commemorates Queen Victoria's Golden Jubilee. Built in the 19th century, this grand colonial structure showcases a blend of Indo-Islamic architecture with its four balconies and Islamic domes. Offering splendid views from the top, it stands as a symbol of Ajmer's history and has witnessed the city's progressions over time. A visit to this marvelous clock tower is a must for anyone exploring Ajmer.
name: Victoria Jubilee Clock Tower
address: Hathi Bhata, Parao, Ajmer, Rajasthan 305001, India

detail_description: Daulat Bagh Rd is a serene oasis in Ajmer, Rajasthan, founded by Emperor Shah Jahan and adorned with lush greenery, vibrant flowers, and stunning marble pavilions. The garden surrounds the picturesque Ana Sagar Lake, offering a tranquil atmosphere for visitors to enjoy boat rides and immerse themselves in the natural beauty. This popular tourist destination provides a peaceful escape from the bustling city life of Ajmer and showcases the historical significance of its surroundings.
name: Daulat Bagh Rd
address: Ajmer, Rajasthan 305001, India

detail_description: The Sai Baba Temple in Ajmer, located at Ajay Nagar, is a relatively recent architectural marvel constructed in 1999. Spanning over two acres, the temple is a popular destination for devotees of Sai Baba. Crafted from pristine marble with translucent qualities that allow light to permeate through, the temple offers a serene and peaceful environment for visitors. It has garnered praise for its cleanliness and tranquil atmosphere, making it an ideal place for families to visit and find solace.
name: Sai Baba Temple
address: 685, Shamshan Ghat Rd, Pahar Ganj, Ajmer, Rajasthan 305001, India

detail_description: The Government Museum in Ajmer is located within the Akbari Fort, offering a fascinating collection of artifacts from the Mughal Emperor Akbar's era. Established in 1908, it features an impressive array of historical items such as stone sculptures, miniature paintings, coins, inscriptions, weapons and armor. The museum also houses exhibits that depict the history of the Rajputs and Ajmer.
name: Government Museum
address: FJ6M+76H, Museum Rd, Gol Pyau, Naya Bazaar, Ajmer, Rajasthan 305001, India

excerpt: Remains of a long-standing Hindu temple, featuring stone carvings, columns & statues.
detail_description: In the town of Pushkar, Rajasthan, lies the Varaha Temple, a significant Hindu temple dedicated to Lord Vishnu's third incarnation, Varaha. Built in the 12th century by King Anaji Chauhan and later reconstructed in the 18th century, it features intricate stone carvings and statues. The temple holds historical importance as it was destroyed by Aurangzeb and rebuilt by Raja Sawai Jai Singh II.
name: Varaha Temple
address: FHR4+8RH, in front of new bus stand, Choti Basti, Pushkar, Rajasthan 305022, India

excerpt: Historical museum at Akbari Fort with military relics, ancient art & light shows at night.
detail_description: Ajmer Fort, also known as Akbar's Palace and Museum, is a significant historical landmark with ties to Mughal emperor Akbar and the British presence in India. Constructed in 1570 AD to honor Sufi saint Khwaja Moin-ud-din Chisti, it offers panoramic views of the Aravalli hills. The fort showcases military relics, ancient art, and hosts light shows at night.
name: Ajmer Fort
address: Naya Bazar, Naya Bazaar, Ajmer, Rajasthan 305001, India

detail_description: Dargah Sharif, located in Ajmer, Rajasthan, is the final resting place of the revered Sufi saint Moinuddin Chishti. Also known as Garib Nawaz, the shrine is a significant Islamic pilgrimage site drawing visitors from around the globe. The majestic tomb was constructed by Emperor Humayun and showcases splendid Mughal architecture with intricate silver carvings adorning its massive doors.
name: Dargah Sharif
address: CJXQ+XX6, Nalasopra, Railway Quarters, Ajmer, Rajasthan 305001, India

detail_description: Rangji Temple is a stunning example of South Indian architecture and Mughal design, making it one of the top places to visit in Pushkar at night. This 18th-century temple is dedicated to Lord Vishnu's incarnation, Rangji, and features a monumental Gopuram and expansive entrance reflecting Dravidian architecture.
name: Rangji Temple
address: FHR4+44Q, Pushkar, Rajasthan 305022, India

detail_description: Akbari Masjid, also known as Akbari Mosque, is a historical site with deep cultural significance. Built by Emperor Akbar in 1570 to express his gratitude for the birth of his son, Prince Salim (Jahangir), this mosque features stunning green and white marble decorations. The serene atmosphere attracts devotees from all over India who come to pray and find peace within its walls.
name: Akbari Masjid
address: FJ4H+Q35, Ander Kote Rd, Khadim Mohalla, Diggi Bazaar, Ajmer, Rajasthan 305001, India

detail_description: Prithvi Raj Chauhan Smarak Parking is a tribute to the valiant Rajput leader, Prithvi Raj Chauhan III. As the final ruler of the Chauhan dynasty in the 12th century, he governed both Ajmer and Delhi. The memorial features a black stone statue of Prithvi Raj III mounted on his horse, with one front hoof raised as if in motion.
name: Samrat Prithvi Raj Chauhan Smarak Parking
address: Prithvi Raj Chauhan Smarak, Ajmer, Rajasthan 305001, India

detail_description: Pushkar Camel Fair is more than just a gathering of camels and horses. It's an opportunity to explore the tranquil town, from its bazaars and Ghats to the holy Pushkar Lake and the country's only Brahma Temple. Visitors can also witness mesmerizing sunrises and sunsets over sand dunes, savor diverse cuisine at lakeside cafes, shop for silver jewelry and traditional clothes, capture vibrant village life through photography, and experience local art performances.
name: Pushkar Camel Fair
address: FGRW+963, Brahma Mandir Rd, Pushkar, Rajasthan 305022, India

detail_description: The Mayo Museum, located within the Jhalwar House of Mayo College in Ajmer, is renowned as the largest school museum globally. Conceived by Mr. TN Vyas, it stands out as a unique institution in the country. As part of Mayo College, it showcases an impressive array of artifacts spanning various fields of study.
name: Mayo Museum
